> The only problem is not the working or the functiosn from the bot. I am thinking more about the users. They love to play around with (the two) bots. And over a long time, it disturbs the main chat extremly IMHO. If there are more than one bot is allowed, we have more problems with "playing around with bots" users. We have a Cbot playground  for this, but often they used the main chat. Because of this, i recommand to allow only one bot in the main chat. If someone want to have her/his own bot for learning or fun, he/she can use the playground chat or private chat rooms, but not the main chat. And if a private bot has functions we wanted for our cbot, the person can help us out with expanding our cbot. 

@Phajava we can rate limit commands to the bot. if you try to send three commands within a short time, the bot will just reply with a link to the playground chatroom.

We could even in future have the bot open a direct message chat with the user in question, so they can play around solo. but that's a bit more coding.

